<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Aye, should only be able to be looted by player if he did the most dmg to you.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Loren">Loren</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:59 p.m. 22/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Aye, should only be able to be looted by player if he did the most dmg to you.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1651" TARGET=_self>Re: Loot: an absurdity</A> (LoneCat)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Same as the way you loot mobs, the player who does most dmg gets to loot. Or some one in group if they are grouped. My pvp server times will be kept short as long as when I die to a mob some one else can take my weapon or armor.

<P>&gt; I have never played a high level character, so I prefer not
<BR>&gt; to discuss the first point. You are probably right =)
<P>&gt; This is a problem indeed.
<P>&gt; Maybe your solution is a bit excessive ?
<P>&gt; Why not simply forbid the loot in case of a monster-kill and put
<BR>&gt; for the loot
<BR>&gt; the same level limitations as for the PvP (+/- 4 lvl) ?
<P>&gt; It would prevent most of the undue loots
<P>&gt; Maybe, we'll see.
<P>&gt; Ciao,
<BR>&gt; LoneCat
<BR>
